# BookDeck UI Replication Prompt (Tailwind)

Use this prompt with any code-generation AI to recreate the same visual system and page architecture for both user and admin UIs.

## Copy-Paste Prompt

You are a senior frontend engineer. Rebuild a web app UI using Tailwind CSS that matches the following design system and layout behavior exactly (or as close as possible).

### 1) Global stack
- Framework-agnostic HTML/JS (plain or React is fine).
- Tailwind CSS CDN style usage.
- Font family: `Inter` (weights 300/400/500/600/700/900).
- Overall visual language: clean, high-contrast, utility-first, rounded cards, subtle shadows.
- Color core:
  - Primary red: `#e30613`
  - Text dark: `#111827` / gray scales (`gray-900..gray-400`)
  - Surface: `white`, background `gray-50`
- Motion:
  - Small fade-in transitions for sections.
  - Hover lift/shadow on key cards.
  - Spinner for loading overlays.

### 2) Shared design tokens (Tailwind utility style)
- Containers:
  - `rounded-2xl` / `rounded-3xl`
  - `border border-gray-100/200`
  - `shadow-sm` (cards), `shadow-lg` (primary CTAs), `shadow-2xl` (modals)
- Inputs:
  - `bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-xl|rounded-2xl`
  - `text-sm font-bold`
  - `focus:border-[#e30613] outline-none`
- Buttons:
  - Primary: `bg-[#e30613] text-white font-bold hover:bg-red-700`
  - Secondary dark: `bg-gray-900 text-white hover:bg-black`
  - Tertiary: light gray with border.
- Labels:
  - Admin form labels mostly `text-[10px] font-black uppercase tracking-widest text-gray-400`
- Sticky/top bars:
  - White background, gray bottom border, subtle shadow.

### 3) User App (`index`) structure

#### 3.1 Login overlay
- Fullscreen fixed overlay (`fixed inset-0 z-[100] bg-white`).
- Centered auth card width around `max-w-md`.
- Brand lockup: BUKit with red `BUK`, dark `it`.
- OTP flow:
  1) email entry
  2) code verify
  3) optional registration sub-steps (student/staff)
- CTA buttons full-width, rounded-xl, red primary.
- Success/error modals with backdrop blur and strong colored header.

#### 3.2 Top navigation
- Sticky top nav (`sticky top-0 z-[45]`) white surface.
- Left: BUKit/Istanbul Bilgi brand treatment.
- Right: links + compact language toggle + admin link badge + sign-out pill button.
- Admin link in red text/border pill.

#### 3.3 Home hero + action cards
- Hero heading with mixed color line:
  - `Book it.` in red
  - `Create it.` in dark
- 4-card grid:
  - Equipment
  - Studio
  - My bookings
  - Ticket (conditionally shown)
- Cards: `bg-white rounded-2xl border shadow-md hover:shadow-lg`, image on top, CTA button at bottom.

#### 3.4 Equipment booking panel
- Large white panel `rounded-2xl shadow-sm border`.
- Date/time controls in responsive grid.
- Category filter bar:
  - Mobile sticky sub-bar near top
  - Red active category chip
  - Search input + compact mode toggle button
- Equipment list appears as stacked groups/cards, with availability states and cart actions.

#### 3.5 Studio area
- Studio cards in single-column responsive stack.
- Embedded/native weekly calendar area with clear busy/free/closed states.
- Form sections for studio booking dates, times, purpose, request type, optional PDF lock logic.

### 4) Admin App (`admin`) structure

#### 4.1 Shell layout
- Full-height app: `body h-screen overflow-hidden`.
- Header (fixed height 64px-ish):
  - Left: logo + red "admin" label
  - Right: user info + "Üye görünümü" + logout buttons
- Main split:
  - Left sidebar fixed width (`w-56 sm:w-64`)
  - Right main workspace scroll container

#### 4.2 Sidebar
- Vertical nav list with emoji-leading labels.
- Active item style:
  - light red background
  - red text
  - right border accent `4px #e30613`
- Pending item has red animated badge.
- Some menu entries visually grouped with `border-t border-gray-100`.

#### 4.3 Admin pages look
- Each page uses `bg-gray-50`, generous padding (`p-6`/`p-8`), white cards.
- Common pages:
  - Traffic (deliver/returns)
  - Quick checkout (left list + right cart panel)
  - Pending approvals
  - Inventory
  - Studio calendar/reservation
  - History / reports / tickets / penalties
- Typography:
  - Section titles usually `text-xl font-black`.
  - Meta text very small uppercase gray.

#### 4.4 Studio admin calendar
- Studio selector grid chips/cards.
- Calendar wrapper:
  - `bg-white rounded-3xl border shadow-sm`
  - Header row with studio icon/name + prev/next week controls
  - Scrollable calendar body
- Busy cell tone: rose/red background.
- Free cell tone: emerald background.
- Selected cell ring accent red.
- Busy cell click opens modal with edit/delete actions.

#### 4.5 Modals and toasts
- Modal backdrop: `fixed inset-0 bg-black/50 backdrop-blur-[1px]`.
- Modal card: white, rounded-2xl, shadow-2xl, border-gray-100.
- Toast stack: bottom-right fixed, short-lived success/error variants.

### 5) Responsive behavior
- Mobile-first.
- Keep form inputs >=16px on small devices to prevent iOS zoom.
- Sidebar stays scrollable (`overflow-y-auto`) while header remains fixed.
- Main content sections independently scrollable.
- Important sticky regions:
  - User top nav
  - Some filter bars on mobile

### 6) Micro-interactions
- Smooth section fade-in.
- Card hover lift.
- Loading skeleton/spinner placeholders.
- Disabled/loading CTA states for async actions.
- Badge pulse for pending count.

### 7) Deliverables
- Build two pages:
  1) `user-app` page
  2) `admin-app` page
- Include reusable component mapping:
  - TopNav, Sidebar, Card, InputField, PrimaryButton, SecondaryButton, Modal, Toast, CalendarGrid, StatusBadge.
- Ensure class naming and utility density resembles a handcrafted Tailwind production app (not minimal demo).

### 8) Must-match visual cues
- Frequent use of `font-black`.
- Red accent `#e30613` for primary actions/highlights.
- Rounded corners (`xl/2xl/3xl`) everywhere.
- White cards on gray-50 canvas.
- Dense yet readable admin console + polished user-facing booking UI.

